
HBaseShell : Shell commands for Examples 1 - 7  

Java code 

To run the Java code : 
1) Add the Hbase jars to your project ($HBASE_HOME/lib)
2) Run directly from the IDE

Class files for the examples
Ex 8: admin.createTable
Ex 9: put.singlePut
Ex 10: put.listPuts
Ex11: get.singleGet
Ex12: get.listGets
Ex13: delete.singleDelete
Ex14: delete.listDeletes
Ex15: batch.batchOp
Ex16: scan.scanRows
Ex17: admin.deleteTable
Ex18: filters.RowFilter
Ex19: filters.colValueFilter
Ex 20: filters.filterList
Ex 21: filters.filterList
Ex 22: counters.counter

NotificationService : notify.Main
MapReduce            : mapReduce.Main

To run MapReduce: 
First create notifications table and add some notifications (use the HBaseShell file to do this)
Then create a summary table
hbase shell> create 'summary','metrics'

Navigate to the folder where you have the jar : Within this source code directory
 "out/artifacts/HBaseJava_jar/"
 
>hadoop jar HBaseJava.jar mapReduce.Main  


